Subject: [PATCH 14/14] Fix RepeatDetection state-save timing (upstream PR #1156)

Upstream issue:  danielmiessler/Personal_AI_Infrastructure#1155
Upstream PR:     danielmiessler/Personal_AI_Infrastructure#1156

hooks/RepeatDetection.hook.ts saves comparison state on every
UserPromptSubmit (line 105), BEFORE checking similarity and BEFORE
the prompt is processed by Claude. As a result:

  1. Cancelled-then-edited prompts cause false positives. If the
     user submits a prompt, cancels Claude mid-response (or before
     it starts), edits the prompt, and resubmits — the hook treats
     the cancelled draft as the comparison baseline and the
     corrected resubmission as a "repeat."

  2. Blocked submissions create an unrecoverable retry loop. When
     the hook fires `exit 2`, it has already written the blocked
     attempt to last-prompt.json. The user's retry is then compared
     against the blocked attempt (necessarily very similar to the
     user's intent), which re-blocks. State keeps refreshing to
     each blocked attempt; user cannot escape without rephrasing
     substantially or manually deleting the state file.

The intended trigger is the user repeating a prompt AFTER Claude
responded — the signal the model missed the user's intent. The
current implementation triggers on the user repeating a prompt
after their previous SUBMISSION ATTEMPT, regardless of whether
Claude saw or responded to it.

Fix (verbatim from upstream PR #1156, applied here as a defensive
package-level patch):

  - hooks/RepeatDetection.hook.ts (UserPromptSubmit): read from
    last-prompt.json (the prompt Claude actually responded to) for
    the comparison; write current submission to a new
    pending-prompt.json instead of overwriting the comparison
    baseline. saveCurrentPrompt → stagePendingPrompt.
  - hooks/RepeatDetectionPromote.hook.ts (NEW Stop hook): when
    Claude finishes responding, promote pending-prompt.json →
    last-prompt.json and delete the pending file.
  - settings.json: register the new Stop hook in the Stop chain.

After the fix:

  - Cancelled / blocked / abandoned prompts never reach Stop, so
    they never become the comparison baseline.
  - Each block compares against the same anchored baseline (the
    last responded-to prompt), so blocks no longer escalate.

Files touched (paths relative to upstream source root):

  Releases/v5.0.0/.claude/hooks/RepeatDetection.hook.ts             :15-17, 72, 79-83, 91, 95, 104-105, 123-126
  Releases/v5.0.0/.claude/hooks/RepeatDetectionPromote.hook.ts      NEW (40 lines, executable)
  Releases/v5.0.0/.claude/settings.json                             :385 (add to Stop chain)

Total: 3 files (2 modified + 1 new), 7 hunks.

Co-existence: patch 0012 modifies settings.json's PostToolUse and
